reviews.comment: 10 Tesla chargers.  Awesome!  Found my new go to hotel in Louisville.
Chargers work fine, most are ICE’d though :(

Tesla's website says that it should provide 16kw. When I plug it in, it shows for a second 80amps and then it switches to 40amps. I told the front desk and they asked the maintenance person. He didn't seem to know much about it and he was annoyed that I mentioned it. 
Update: Tesla customer support says that when the car senses significant fluctuation in the current, it drops the amperage until the power stabilizes. I guess the hotel has 80A but unstable circuit.
Trying out new  charger.  It's on and operating fine. It appears the tesla chargers have power as well.
None of the chargers have been wired, still have plastic on them and no power.
